item.title: This is secound time iask this question and idont get answear!
item.dc:creator: @baselm baselm
item.description:
@baselm wrote:

go to gui.java and there will be something like this after 20 lines i guess
Serverip = “YYYYYYY.no-ip.biz”; with a different ip , change it to ur ip if u portforwarded if not change it to 127.0.0.1.
if u dont have gui.java and u have EGUI.java then open egui.java and u will see 3 same ips, change them all to 127.0.0.1 or to ur ip if u portforwarded, if u dont have either gui.java or egui.java
then search at client.java for no-ip or ip until u see an ip and change it to 127.0.0.1 or to ur ip

item.dc:creator: @Projext Projext
item.description:
@Projext wrote:

go into the client files, and look for client.java, in their search for the IP that it connects to and change it to “127.0.0.1” or “0.0.0.0” and check that the port for you server and client are “43594” or both the same, doesn’t matter on the numbers.
